                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kampaṇa Uḍaiyar. Ś. 1291, Saumya: 1369 A.D. Kampaṇa Uḍaiyar is stated to be the son of Vīra Bokkaṇa Uḍaiyar. The details of date given, viz., Śaka 1291, Saumya, Tulā śu. 13, Sunday, Uttiraṭṭādi correspond to 1369 A.D., October 14, Sunday, the <hi rend="italic">nakshatra</hi> Uttiraṭṭādi having ended at 92, the previous day.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the remission of the levy of <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭu-viṉiyōgam</hi> on the <hi rend="italic">kāṉi</hi> land, Vīrapālaṉēndal in Araivariśaippaṟṟu belonging to Nāyaṉār Peṇṇorubāga-mudaliyār of Maruttūr, by the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭār</hi> in Vaḍagarai in Magadai-maṇḍalam.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
